  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>re: MediaWiki format: There is the "mvs" command line tool for interacting with
MediaWiki wikis, for what it's worth.

There's also the pure-Python
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/mwclient/index.php?title=Main_Page">http://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/mwclient/index.php?title=Main_Page</a> , which
is a reasonable wrapper around the MediaWiki API.

I have no idea which would be simpler to add, so I'll leave that to you as a
thought on the ticket. (-:</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg997">msg997 (view)</a></th>
